# Frontend design system per app (awaits ADR-08)

## Rule
Until ADR-08 resolves, each app keeps its design system:

- **freightify-web, admin-frontend** → PrimeNG / PrimeReact.
- **extraction-frontend** → Tailwind only, no component library.
- **quote-ai-frontend** → shadcn/ui on Tailwind.
- **fb-shipper-frontend, fb-documents** → legacy Angular-native components.

New components use the app's existing system.

## Why
Mixing libraries inside one app produces double style bundles, inconsistent keyboard / a11y behavior, and a cluttered dependency tree. ADR-08 decides the long-term direction; in the meantime, apps stay coherent.

## Constraints
- Don't introduce a second component library into an existing app.
- Shared brand tokens (colors, type scale, spacing) — if produced — live in a shared package and are consumed as variables, not as a second component library.
- Custom components wrap the app's library's primitives (`<PrimeButton>`, `<shadcn/Button>`) rather than re-rolling them.
- Accessibility expectations (keyboard nav, ARIA roles) travel with the library's idioms.

## Examples

### Good
> New quote-ai-frontend dialog uses `shadcn/Dialog` with Tailwind utility classes; matches existing app idioms.

### Bad
> New quote-ai-frontend dialog pulls in `@primer/react` "because it has a nicer modal."

